10 AS INTRODUCED
11 An Act relating to public meetings; amending 25 O.S.
2021, Section 307.1, as last amended by Section 3,
12 Chapter 369, O.S.L. 2025 (25 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
307.1), which relates to videoconference exceptions;
13 providing exception for the State Committee of Blind
Vendors; requiring members to be audible or visible;
14 providing information meeting notice shall contain;
and declaring an emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 25 O.S. 2021, Section 307.1, as
19 last amended by Section 3, Chapter 369, O.S.L. 2025 (25 O.S. Supp.
20 2025, Section 307.1), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 307.1. A. A public body may hold meetings by
22 videoconference where each member of the public body is visible and
23 audible to each other and the public through a video monitor,
24 subject to the following:
HB3627 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 1. a. except as provided for in subparagraph b of this
2 paragraph, no less than a quorum of the public body
3 shall be present in person at the meeting site as
4 posted on the meeting notice and agenda,
5 b. a virtual charter school approved and sponsored by the
6 Statewide Charter School Board pursuant to the
7 provisions of Section 3-132.1 of Title 70 of the
8 Oklahoma Statutes, or the Statewide Independent Living
9 Council established pursuant to Section 625.2 of Title
10 56 of the Oklahoma Statutes, or the State Committee of
11 Blind Vendors established pursuant to Section 78 of
12 Title 7 of the Oklahoma Statutes shall maintain a
13 quorum of members for the entire duration of the
14 meeting whether using an in-person site,
15 videoconference sites or any combination of such sites
16 to achieve a quorum, and
17 c. each public meeting held by videoconference or
18 teleconference shall be recorded either by written,
19 electronic, or other means;
20 2. The meeting notice and agenda prepared in advance of the
21 meeting, as required by law, shall indicate if the meeting will
22 include videoconferencing locations and shall state:
23 a. the location, address, and telephone number of each
24 available videoconference site, and
HB3627 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 b. the identity of each member of the public body and the
2 specific site from which each member of the body shall
3 be physically present and participating in the
4 meeting;
5 3. After the meeting notice and agenda are prepared and posted,
6 as required by law, no member of the public body shall be allowed to
7 participate in the meeting from any location other than the specific
8 location posted on the agenda in advance of the meeting;
9 4. In order to allow the public the maximum opportunity to
10 attend and observe each public official carrying out the duties of
11 the public official, a member or members of a public body desiring
12 to participate in a meeting by videoconference shall participate in
13 the videoconference from a site and room located within the district
14 or political subdivision from which they are elected, appointed, or
15 are sworn to represent;
16 5. Each site and room where a member of the public body is
17 present for a meeting by videoconference shall be open and
18 accessible to the public, and the public shall be allowed into that
19 site and room. Public bodies may provide additional videoconference
20 sites as a convenience to the public, but additional sites shall not
21 be used to exclude or discourage public attendance at any
22 videoconference site;
23 6. The public shall be allowed to participate and speak, as
24 allowed by rule or policy set by the public body, in a meeting at
HB3627 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 the videoconference site in the same manner and to the same extent
2 as the public is allowed to participate or speak at the site of the
3 meeting;
4 7. Unless confidential or privileged under applicable law, any
5 materials shared electronically between members of the public body,
6 before or during the videoconference, shall also be immediately
7 available to the public in the same form and manner as shared with
8 members of the public body; and
9 8. All votes occurring during any meeting conducted using
10 videoconferencing shall occur and be recorded by roll call vote.
11 B. Except as provided for in subsections C and D of this
12 section, no public body shall conduct an executive session by
13 videoconference.
14 C. The Oklahoma Tax Commission may conduct executive sessions
15 with the taxpayer at issue attending using videoconference
16 technology to discuss confidential taxpayer matters as provided for
17 in Section 205 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes. During
18 executive sessions, the Commission is required to be physically
19 present while taxpayers may appear using videoconference technology.
20 The technology selected and utilized by the Commission shall ensure
21 taxpayer confidentiality including compliance with safeguards as
22 provided for in Internal Revenue Service Publication 1075.
23 D. The Statewide Independent Living Council established
24 pursuant to Section 625.2 of Title 56 of the Oklahoma Statutes may
HB3627 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 cond uct executive sessions using videoconference technology. For
2 such executive sessions, no Council member shall be required to be
3 physically present as long as each Council member is audible or
4 visible to each other. The meeting notice and agenda prepared in
5 advance of the meeting as required by law shall indicate if the
6 executive session will include videoconferencing and shall also
7 state the identity of each Council member appearing remotely, and
8 whether any member will be physically present at the meeting site,
9 if any, for the executive session.
10 E. The State Committee of Blind Vendors established pursuant to
11 Section 78 of Title 7 of the Oklahoma Statues may conduct executive
12 sessions using videoconference technology. For such executive
13 sessions, no Committee member shall be required to be physically
14 present as long as each Committee member is audible or visible to
15 other members participating in the executive session. The meeting
16 notice and agenda prepared in advance of the meeting as required by
17 law shall indicate whether the executive session will include
18 videoconferencing, shall state the identity of each Committee member
19 appearing remotely, and shall note whether any member will be
20 physically present at the meeting site, if any, for the executive
21 session.
22 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
24
HB3627 HFLR Page 5
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 decl ared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
2 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
